[1
Date: Thu, 19 Aug 1999 16:19:28 +0200
From: tropmed.marine@t-online.de

We had been responsible for the preparation of the medical personnel
of the German Contingents on infectious diseases in the Kosovo area
and we, of course, mentioned the possible CCHF threat there.
Before giving a warning to the doctors in the field and the commanding
officers and initiating an alert on that CCHF case, it is important to know
more details. When? Where? Who? Which circumstances? Laboratory
confirmed? There are a lot of possible differential diagnoses.
--
Dr. Gerhard Boecken, MD
Commander (MC)
The German Navy Institute for Maritime Medicine
Division I/3, Infectious Diseases
Tropical and Preventive Medicine Surveillance Unit
