[3
Date: Wed, 18 Aug 1999 21:55:43 -0400
From: "Peters, C.J." <cjp0@cdc.gov>

Given the activity of CCHF elsewhere, it might well be [CCHF
-- CCHF is well documented in the area -- and the nosocomial danger
needs to be looked at.
However, the possibility of HFRS from Dobrava is also there. There
has been a lot more HFRS diagnosed than CCHF in the last decade
(good for betting, but not so good for knowing what's really going on).
--
C.J.Peters
Chief, Special Pathogens Laboratory
Centers for Disease Control & Prevention
Atlanta, GA, USA
<cjp0@cdc.gov>
[CJ is referring to hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome, caused
by Dobrava virus. Bo Niklasson, do you have a comment? - Mod.JW
